        <updateDate>2023-05-08T14:32:32Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Autonomy for Disabled Veterans Act</strong></p> <p>This bill increases the maximum amount authorized under the Home Improvements and Structural Alterations (HISA) grant program to $10,000 for veterans with a service-connected disability and $5,000 for those with disabilities that are not service-connected. The HISA grant program provides medically necessary improvements and structural alterations to veterans' (or service members') primary residence for specified purposes (e.g., allowing for entrance to their home).</p> <p>The bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs to increase the dollar amount of the grant in accordance with inflation as determined by the Consumer Price Index.<br> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
